# PR Creation Rules

- [ ] The PR title must begin with the issue ID, followed by the exact issue title.
  - Example:
    - Issue ID: GET-5
    - Issue title: Update calendar input box on the frontend
    - Expected output: `GET-5 Update calendar input behavior`
- [ ] The branch name must begin with the issue ID, followed by a short, descriptive slug.
  - Example:
    - Issue ID: GET-5
    - Issue title: Update calendar input box on the frontend
    - Expected output: `GET-5-update-calendar-input`
- [ ] The PR description should follow the template in `<project_root>/.github/pr_template.md`

# Commit Rules

- [ ] Each commit message must begin with the issue id, followed by a valid commit type (`feat`, `fix`, or `chore`).
- [ ] The commit description must clearly and succinctly state the change introduced.
- [ ] Example:
  - Issue ID: GET-5
  - Issue title: Update calendar input box on the frontend
  - Expected commit message: `GET-5 fix: Update calendar input box on the frontend`s
